The paper deals with text recognition and retrieval in natural images, which is a task commonly studied in computer vision (cs.CV). Additionally, the paper proposes a convolutional neural network (CNN) for learning a joint embedding space for word images and semantic concepts, which is a common approach in natural language processing (cs.CL). The use of a lexical database (WordNet) also suggests a connection to information retrieval (cs.IR). The paper's focus on learning a weighted ranking loss objective and end-to-end learning also suggests a connection to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
